//! Conformance suite for `ferrotorch-train` — Layer 3.
//!
//! Tracking issue: #843 (ferrotorch-train conformance suite).
//!
//! Reference library: `torch` (training utilities), pinned to
//! `torch == 2.11.0`. Fixtures live in
//! `tests/conformance/fixtures.json`, generated by
//! `scripts/regenerate_train_fixtures.py`.
//!
//! ## Scope
//!
//! Every public item in `ferrotorch-train` that can be exercised without a
//! live GPU, model, or data pipeline falls into one of two groups:
//!
//! 1. **Fixture-driven** — items whose correct behaviour is fully determined by
//!    reference outputs stored in `fixtures.json`. These tests load the fixture
//!    file, drive the ferrotorch implementation with the same inputs, and assert
//!    numerical agreement.
//!
//! 2. **cascade_skip — Learner::fit / live training required** — items that
//!    require a constructed model, optimizer, and data iterator. These are
//!    skipped with a one-line diagnostic and a tracking issue reference.
//!
//! ## cascade_skip convention
//!
//! `cascade_skip!(label)` prints a diagnostic and returns early. It is NOT
//! `#[ignore]` — the test still runs and emits the notice. This matches the
//! ferrotorch-xpu and ferrotorch-mps conformance pattern (no silent skips).

#![allow(
    clippy::cast_possible_truncation,
    clippy::cast_precision_loss,
    clippy::cast_sign_loss,
    clippy::uninlined_format_args,
    clippy::explicit_iter_loop,
    clippy::redundant_else
)]

